While GPS technology allows us to pinpoint any location on the planet, mark the location, and share it with others, Waymarking is the toolset for categorizing and adding unique information for that location.

3047 Goethe & Johann Wolfgang von Goethe, Hasištejn Castle, Czechia

in Extraterrestrial Locations

Posted by: ashberry

N 50° 26.703 E 013° 15.435

33U E 376262 N 5589566

Planetka nacházející se v hlavním pásu asteroidu // Asteroid in the main asteroid belt

Waymark Code: WM11XKJ

Location: Ústecký kraj, Czechia

Views: 13

CZ: 3047 Goethe je planetka nacházející se v hlavním pásu asteroidu. Objevili ji van Houten, C. J., van Houten-Groeneveld, I., Gehrels, T. 24. zárí 1960. Byla pojmenována podle nemeckého básníka J.W. von Goetheho. Kolem Slunce obehne jednou za 4,298 let.

Reliéf s podobiznou Johanna Wolfganga von Goetha (1749-1832) (visit link) na desce pripomínající básníkovu návštevu na hrade Hasistejn v roce 1810. Reliéf byl umísten na skále v roce 1910.

EN: 3047 Goethe, provisional designation 6091 P-L, is a bright background asteroid from the central regions of the asteroid belt, approximately 6 kilometers (3.7 miles) in diameter. It was discovered on 24 September 1960, by Dutch astronomer couple Ingrid and Cornelis van Houten on photographic plates taken by Dutch–American astronomer Tom Gehrels at the Palomar Observatory in California, United States. The asteroid was named after German poet Johann Wolfgang von Goethe.

Relief with a portrait of Johann Wolfgang von Goethe (1749-1832) (visit link) on a plate commemorating the poet's visit to Hasistejn Castle in 1810. The relief was placed on a rock in 1910.
